reviewText: I don't like this format with the still photographs -- I prefer video which matches the sound.
This put me to sleep in 10 minutes and I wasn't even sleepy.

Okay - on my new Samsung HD television, there is a low frequency noise that's awful. But that television has an issue with low frequency. My husband noticed it in movies - I don't really notice it. But this video REALLY made it show up. Cannot tolerate it.

Just to check that out, I played it on my computer. Sounds fine - sounds like a beach. The low frequency problem is gone. So it must be our TV.

If you like beach sounds, this might be just the thing for you.

The sounds are good, no extra background noises to ruin the ambiance. But I agree with the other reviewer, I don't like the stills. It feels disjointed and awkward, and sometimes shows a city shoreline which feels really out of sync with the ocean sounds. It is fine if you use it strictly as noise while sleeping, or for closed eye meditation, but if I wanted that I would just use my sound machine and use way less power! I saw that it said images and not video in the description, but the other releases from this company are video, so I don't understand why this one is different. I also feel it is a little short. I suppose I will have to try and find another video to use during therapy sessions, and if someone were looking to use it for sleep, I think I would still rather recommend playing a soundtrack through a stereo rather than turning on your tv and streaming device to use this. But I do recommend trying some of the other videos from this company. I have not seen them all yet, but if this is the worst of the group, thats not bad at all!
